  "measurement_note": "Size is S = R*C, the number of cells. Each legal two-row grid is one layer and uses k = S/2, so the effective shift is proportional to its perimeter. Direct modular placement is O(S). A correct slower implementation first reduces k modulo the perimeter, then materializes each remaining one-position rotation in O(S), completing every case but failing only by O(S^2) scaling.",
